XXXIII. A comical complaint of the lightness and thin- ness of a phiala sent as a present to the poet by his rich friend Paulus. The point of the epigram lies in the last two lines. It is intended to show up the stupidity of rich men, who thought to keep up their reputation, as noble patrous, by giving presents not worth having.

1. praetoricia...corona. A chaplet of sssver or gold pre- sented by the praetor as a prize at the games. The praetors under the empire had the whole charge of the state games.
